cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CR, cs.DS

This paper is about developing accurate models that can also be explained to humans. It focuses on identifying a maximal set of distinct but accurate models for a dataset, which is a problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) since the paper deals with developing interpretable models. Additionally, since the paper deals with classification, it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
